Indian and Pakistani military officials were set to discuss ceasefire violations over the Line of Control.
Despite tensions, a bus service was launched to reunite Kashmiris separated for decades.
Indian Prime Minister Singh expressed a commitment to peace and announced a development plan for the region.
Pakistani President Musharraf suggested potential solutions for Kashmir.
The bus service, symbolizing peace, allowed Kashmiris to meet after years of separation.
Kashmiri leaders emphasized the need for their involvement in peace talks.
The prime ministers of India and Pakistan aimed to find compromises in the Kashmir conflict.
India and Pakistan are gradually moving towards a potential resolution for the benefit of their people.
